<br>
Sigh...<br>
<br>
Ok, here is a graph of my Ragebringer mainhand.  15 damage weapon, 9 damage bonus back when I made this log in December:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://64.81.174.43/pics/pierce.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Notice the nice prominant spike at 39.  A weapon's mode is is always 2x+y, where x is the base damage, and y is the damage bonus.  Plug in the numbers and, yup, (2*15)+9=39.<br>
<br>
Now, what does this mean for elemental damage?  Well, it either adds to the base damage or the damage bonus.  If it's a bonus, the new formula is 2x+y+z.  Plug in the numbers for a LSoEE in the offhand, and we have (2*16)+0+(0..5).  The graph would show a plateau across 32 to 37.  How high the individual peaks are within the plateau depends on the resist rate, but those six numbers should still be a fair bit above the surroundings.<br>
<br>
If it adds to the base, it's 2*(x+z)+y.  That makes a LSoEE 2*(16+(0..5))+0, and we should see alternating peaks and valleys starting with 32 and ending with 42.<br>
<br>
Now here's the graph of my LSoEE, offhand over the same period as the Ragebringer above.  Which equation do the peaks fit?<br>
<br>
